# This directory holds the file CURRENTLY being cataloged.
#
# Three-directory model for the cataloging pipeline:
#   raw/queue/         — PENDING. Staged, not yet promoted.
#   static/in-flight/  — IN_PROGRESS. Currently being cataloged.
#   static/originals/  — CATALOGED. Completed files stay here permanently.
#
# At most one file should ever be in this directory at a time. If you
# see more than one, something has gone wrong (a workflow run died
# mid-catalog and a manual recovery is needed, OR a concurrency-group
# misconfiguration let two runs race).
#
# Recovery from a stuck file:
#   - Move it back to raw/queue/ to retry.
#   - Move it to static/originals/ to mark as failed (status=FAILED on
#     the Acquisition page, since no source page will exist).
#   - Or delete it entirely if it shouldn't be cataloged at all.
#
# Files in this directory ARE downloadable via /api/originals/<filename>
# (the download endpoint checks both static/originals/ and
# static/in-flight/), so you can inspect what's mid-catalog if needed.
